# Commit And Push Workflow

- After making code changes, commit and push to GitHub in the same task by default.
- Use clear commit messages that reflect the purpose of the change.
- Do not push only when the user explicitly says not to commit/push for that task.
- Before pushing, run relevant verification for the touched area when feasible.
- Never commit secrets or environment tokens.
